@startuml states-signature-lifecycle
!include ../_includes/style.iuml

title State machine — Signature.characterization_state lifecycle

' States are the literal values on disk in `.ts/<file>.json`.
' Transitions correspond to characterizeRunner.ts outcomes.
'
' Companion artifacts written next to the signature JSON:
'   - `.ts/<file>.log`              — active session: llama-server
'                                     stdout/stderr captured on every
'                                     Maestria-managed launch
'                                     (append-only, 4 MiB rotation).
'   - `.ts/<file>.<YYYYMMDDThhmmssZ>.log`
'                                   — per-session archive (2026-05-24):
'                                     rotated from `.log` at the start
'                                     of each new characterization,
'                                     keeps last 10 sessions per model.
'   - `.ts/<file>.error`            — timestamped per-model error
'                                     journal from characterizeAll
'                                     (one line per failure).
' All best-effort writes: a disk error never sinks a run.

[*] --> NotCharacterized : model added\nto folder

state "Not characterized" as NotCharacterized {
  description : sidecar `modelMeta` exists\n(possibly with autoTags)\nbut no `signature` field.\nFor routing: D9 ⇒ INELIGIBLE.
}

NotCharacterized --> Running : user clicks\n"Caractériser"\nOR MCP request

state "Running (in-progress)" as Running {
  description : characterizeRunner active.\nlistRunning() shows the chat\nprocess; characterization_state\non disk still null (no partial\nwrites).
}

Running --> Complete : R5 + tree + freegen\n(if seamed)\nALL succeeded
Running --> Incomplete : R5 OK\nbut tree OR freegen\nfailed (isolated)
Running --> Quarantined : R5 itself failed\n(e.g. model crashed boot)\nOR catastrophic IO error\nOR non-chat model detected\n(3-tier filter, 2026-05-24)

state "complete" as Complete #FFFDF6 {
  description : routing-eligible (D9).\nAll required behavioral fields\npresent: `scores_per_axis`,\n`scores_per_leaf`, `branch_scores`.\nmodels.route ranks this candidate.
}

state "incomplete" as Incomplete {
  description : routing-eligible (D9) iff\nthe core scores_per_axis is set.\nMissing optional fields ⇒\ndegraded confidence but ranked.
}

state "quarantined" as Quarantined #E6DFD2 {
  description : routing INELIGIBLE.\nShown in radar with a clear\nbanner. User re-characterizes\nto leave this state.
}

Complete --> Running : Re-caractériser\n(with confirm)
Incomplete --> Running : Re-caractériser
Quarantined --> Running : Re-caractériser
Complete --> Stale : modelHash drift\n(file edited /\nshards changed)
Incomplete --> Stale : modelHash drift

state "Stale" as Stale {
  description : Pseudo-state: hash on disk ≠\ncurrent file hash. Routing\nstill uses old signature but\nUI prompts re-characterization.
}

Stale --> Running : Re-caractériser

note bottom of Quarantined
  Quarantined remains permanent
  until the user explicitly
  re-characterizes — even if a
  routing query comes in.
end note

note right of Running
  Side-effects on disk:
  • `archiveServerLog(...)` at run START
    (renames previous `.log` →
    `.<ISO>.log`, fresh session
    begins clean — 2026-05-24).
  • `appendServerLog(.log, chunk)`
    on every llama-server stdout/stderr
    chunk (hooked in runners/launch.ts).
  • On Quarantined / Incomplete-with-error:
    `appendErrorLog(.ts/<file>.error,
    reason)` with ISO timestamp.
end note

@enduml
